      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C fan. Grease a 20×20 cm tin and line with baking paper.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt butter and sugar",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt the {{unsalted-butter}} in a medium saucepan over low heat. Remove from the heat and stir in the {{light-brown-sugar}} until dissolved. Leave to cool for 10 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Add eggs and flour",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat in the {{free-range-eggs}} one at a time, then the {{vanilla-extract}}. Stir in the {{plain-flour}}, {{baking-powder}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}} until just combined. Fold in the {{white-chocolate-chips}} if using.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 22 to 25 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour the batter into the tin and spread to the corners. Bake for 22 to 25 minutes. The blondie is ready when the edges are set and the centre gives a very slight wobble when you shake the tin. A skewer through the centre should come out with damp crumbs rather than clean. Do not overbake.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cool in the tin for 30 minutes before cutting. The blondie firms as it cools and cuts cleanly only when it is at room temperature.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
